        "title": "fix(ui): hide thinking options for non-reasoning models",
        "body": "Summary:\n- Hide override thinking choices when the selected model is known not to support reasoning.\n- Collapse off-only session/default thinking levels and persisted Off overrides back to inherited Off.\n- Add a regression for the duplicate-Off Control UI selector state.\n\nFixes #84069. Thanks @DrippingMellow.\n\nBehavior addressed: Control UI chat thinking selector showed duplicate Off choices and stayed enabled for catalog-known non-reasoning models.\nReal environment tested: local Node 24.13.0 module-level selector proof; local formatter/check proof.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: node --import tsx direct resolveChatThinkingSelectState proof for a known non-reasoning Ollama model with off-only thinkingLevels and persisted thinkingLevel=off; pnpm exec oxfmt --check ui/src/ui/chat/session-controls.ts ui/src/ui/views/chat.test.ts; git diff --check; .agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local.\nEvidence after fix: resolveChatThinkingSelectState returns no override options and an inherited Off label for the known non-reasoning model, while unknown models keep the fallback Off option.\nObserved result after fix: the selector renders disabled with only Inherited: Off instead of duplicate Off choices.\nWhat was not tested: full browser/CI UI lane locally; focused Vitest prebundle stalled before test execution, so CI owns the normal suite.\n\n\nCI follow-up:\n- Rebased onto current origin/main and refreshed generated npm shrinkwrap files because the shared shrinkwrap guard reported current generated drift unrelated to the UI code path.\n- Additional proof: pnpm deps:shrinkwrap:root:check passed after generation; targeted oxlint and selector proof stayed green.\n",
